:''Not to be confused with the New York City-based arts organization [[Imagenation]], nor [[ImaginAsian]].''
'''Image Nation''', formerly known as '''Imagenation Abu Dhabi''', is an Emirati film production and media company that is a subsidiary of the governmental Media Zone Authority Abu Dhabi (MZA) based at [[twofour54]] in [[Abu Dhabi]], the [[United Arab Emirates]]. It was founded in 2007 as a platform for development of regional talent and productions and has two divisions, '''Image Nation Abu Dhabi''' and '''Image Nation International''' for co-production of international films etc. The company was renamed Image Nation in October 2011 and formed those two divisions.<ref>{{cite journal | last=Lodderhose | first=Diana | url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1118043777 | title=Imagenation rebrands, restructures | journal=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] | date=October 3, 2011 }}</ref> Image Nation is led by Mohamed Al Mubarak, Chairman of the Board for Image Nation, and Michael Garin, Chief Executive Officer.
